cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.TL, cs.FL, cs.SE

This paper deals with type-level computation and type families, which are concepts closely related to programming languages and type theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also presents a new design for type families that simplifies their metatheory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.TL (Computational Logic). Additionally, the paper discusses the type safety of the proposed approach, which could place it in cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
